00:13:28.900 --> 00:13:30.580
AJAY DEVGN: Yes.

00:13:30.580 --> 00:13:39.380
In fact, my father is, and
was, the most respected action

00:13:39.380 --> 00:13:42.081
director in our country, and--

00:13:42.081 --> 00:13:43.580
KAJOL: He invented
so much, himself.

00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:44.913
AJAY DEVGN: He invented so much.

00:13:44.913 --> 00:13:46.870
KAJOL: As far as film
making was concerned--

00:13:46.870 --> 00:13:49.300
AJAY DEVGN: When the effects
and CGI was not there.

00:13:49.300 --> 00:13:51.792
I mean, he did films
like "Mr. India."

00:13:51.792 --> 00:13:53.750
I don't know if you all
have seen a film called

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:54.460
"Mr. India," which was--

00:13:54.460 --> 00:13:55.293
PAVNI DIWANJI: Yeah.

00:13:55.293 --> 00:13:55.810
Yeah.

00:13:55.810 --> 00:13:56.310
Yeah.

00:13:56.310 --> 00:13:57.450
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:13:57.450 --> 00:14:00.670
AJAY DEVGN: And at that point
of time, it was all live.

00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:03.360
So you couldn't cheat.

00:14:03.360 --> 00:14:05.270
And he could manage
doing a lot of things.

00:14:05.270 --> 00:14:07.930
And I was eight, nine years old.

00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:10.027
And when I used to keep
discussing with him,

00:14:10.027 --> 00:14:11.860
and he used to come and
tell me, I did this.

00:14:11.860 --> 00:14:12.980
Tell me how.

00:14:12.980 --> 00:14:14.890
And that's how the
whole process started.

00:14:14.890 --> 00:14:17.950
By the age of 12, I
was editing with him.

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:18.450
And--

00:14:18.450 --> 00:14:20.410
KAJOL: And editing,
at that point of time,

00:14:20.410 --> 00:14:22.610
was not with a mouse.

00:14:22.610 --> 00:14:23.660
So it was actually--

00:14:23.660 --> 00:14:24.340
AJAY DEVGN: Oh,
it was actually--

00:14:24.340 --> 00:14:24.970
KAJOL: --frame by frame.

00:14:24.970 --> 00:14:26.678
AJAY DEVGN: A machine
called the Moviola.

00:14:26.678 --> 00:14:28.910
So you had to hold the reel.

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:29.785
And you had to stand.

00:14:29.785 --> 00:14:31.210
And there was a small monitor.

00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:31.899
And you had to--

00:14:31.899 --> 00:14:32.690
PAVNI DIWANJI: Wow.

00:14:32.690 --> 00:14:33.648
KAJOL: Press the pedal.

00:14:33.648 --> 00:14:35.760
AJAY DEVGN: Like
the accelerator.

00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:38.500
We had to stand, and keep
rolling with our hands.

00:14:38.500 --> 00:14:42.580
And, I mean, actually cut
the frame and join it.

00:14:42.580 --> 00:14:44.580
KAJOL: Actually cut the
frame of the film print.

00:14:44.580 --> 00:14:46.820
AJAY DEVGN: So it was a very
different process altogether.

00:14:46.820 --> 00:14:48.111
So we've gone through all that.

00:14:48.111 --> 00:14:51.840
And at that point of time, I
started making films myself,

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:56.520
also, and obviously,
I couldn't afford it,

00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:59.220
so-- But I started
making my own equipments

00:14:59.220 --> 00:15:02.850
at that point of time, where
I could take shots, which

00:15:02.850 --> 00:15:05.150
so many people, at
that point of time,

00:15:05.150 --> 00:15:08.990
he used to see those small
videos of mine, and say, OK.

00:15:08.990 --> 00:15:12.640
I will go all my
father's friends, saying,

00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:14.944
can I use this shot in a film?

00:15:14.944 --> 00:15:15.860
I'm going to copy you.

00:15:15.860 --> 00:15:16.970
Said, go ahead.

00:15:16.970 --> 00:15:17.960
So it was like this.

00:15:17.960 --> 00:15:19.090
That is the whole process.

00:15:19.090 --> 00:15:22.540
So I think, because of my
father, I learned a lot.

00:15:22.540 --> 00:15:27.450
And I tried to create things
which were not possible, also.

00:15:27.450 --> 00:15:29.700
PAVNI DIWANJI: Yeah, I mean,
it shows in the trailer--

00:15:29.700 --> 00:15:30.610
AJAY DEVGN: And
nowadays, it's become--

00:15:30.610 --> 00:15:30.820
PAVNI DIWANJI: --how different--

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:32.403
AJAY DEVGN: --a lot
more easier, also,

00:15:32.403 --> 00:15:34.615
with the effects, and
lots of things coming in.

00:15:34.615 --> 00:15:36.490
But at that point of
time, there was nothing.

00:15:36.490 --> 00:15:37.948
PAVNI DIWANJI: How
different it is.

00:15:37.948 --> 00:15:40.390
I feel like you are going
to single-handedly raise

00:15:40.390 --> 00:15:41.447
the bar on Bollywood.

00:15:41.447 --> 00:15:42.780
AJAY DEVGN: Not single-handedly.

00:15:42.780 --> 00:15:43.520
PAVNI DIWANJI: [INAUDIBLE]

00:15:43.520 --> 00:15:45.200
AJAY DEVGN: I think
the whole team--

00:15:45.200 --> 00:15:45.620
PAVNI DIWANJI: Team.

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:46.040
Team.

00:15:46.040 --> 00:15:46.330
Yeah.

00:15:46.330 --> 00:15:47.579
AJAY DEVGN: --very big effort.

00:15:47.579 --> 00:15:49.260
PAVNI DIWANJI: I
think the thing that

00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:54.530
struck me here was, it's
quite an action-packed film.

00:15:54.530 --> 00:15:57.090
AJAY DEVGN: Honestly,
it's an emotional drama.

00:15:57.090 --> 00:16:00.290
But if you notice the
action part of it,

00:16:00.290 --> 00:16:02.740
also, it's not just
for the sake of it.

00:16:02.740 --> 00:16:05.810
And there is pain on
the face, on my face,

00:16:05.810 --> 00:16:08.574
also, and the other actors,
also, who are doing action

00:16:08.574 --> 00:16:09.490
at that point of time.

00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:12.670
So it's actually a very
real kind of thing.

00:16:12.670 --> 00:16:14.360
PAVNI DIWANJI: Wow.

00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:16.460
One of the things I was
talking in the hallway,

00:16:16.460 --> 00:16:19.720
and someone mentioned
that you have always

00:16:19.720 --> 00:16:23.870
been at the forefront
of this action drama.

00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:27.845
Like Arnold Schwarzenegger come
to mind, for Bollywood, right?

00:16:27.845 --> 00:16:28.720
Would you guys agree?

00:16:28.720 --> 00:16:31.475
AUDIENCE: [APPLAUSE]

00:16:31.475 --> 00:16:32.600
PAVNI DIWANJI: And I also--

00:16:32.600 --> 00:16:34.248
KAJOL: Better accent, though.

00:16:34.248 --> 00:16:39.900
PAVNI DIWANJI: [LAUGHS] And
I read that, a lot of times,

00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:42.210
you like even doing
the stunts yourself,

00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:44.450
and to figure out how
these stunts are done.

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:50.990
So you are not just like
tough guy on the screen,

00:16:50.990 --> 00:16:52.642
but you're actually
trying to live it.

00:16:52.642 --> 00:16:54.350
AJAY DEVGN: Actually,
that is by default,

00:16:54.350 --> 00:16:59.780
because when I started
acting, my first film came in.

00:16:59.780 --> 00:17:04.400
As I told you, I am an
action director's son.

00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:07.130
So they expected me to
do the action myself.

00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:08.910
They did not-- they
thought-- I mean,

00:17:08.910 --> 00:17:10.869
he would not need a duplicate.

00:17:10.869 --> 00:17:13.290
And I was practiced
for it, because

00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:15.609
of my father and his
whole team and everything.

00:17:15.609 --> 00:17:19.200
So, actually, it was by
default. So I was pushed into it

00:17:19.200 --> 00:17:21.200
that, you know, you're
an action director's son,

00:17:21.200 --> 00:17:23.100
so you have to do
your action yourself.

00:17:23.100 --> 00:17:26.030
PAVNI DIWANJI: [LAUGHS] Well,
great results, we have to say.

00:17:26.030 --> 00:17:26.530
[INAUDIBLE]

00:17:26.530 --> 00:17:27.660
AJAY DEVGN: And then
I started enjoying it.

00:17:27.660 --> 00:17:28.367
And now--

00:17:28.367 --> 00:17:30.200
PAVNI DIWANJI: "Shivaay,"
"Singham," I mean,

00:17:30.200 --> 00:17:31.852
there's so-- there's a whole--

00:17:31.852 --> 00:17:32.560
AJAY DEVGN: Yeah.

00:17:32.560 --> 00:17:36.610
And now it's been 25
years in the industry,

00:17:36.610 --> 00:17:38.090
so when I started, I was 19.

00:17:38.090 --> 00:17:39.750
I'm like 47 now.

00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:41.700
And now I like
doing my own stunts,

00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:44.230
trying to prove a point--
what the duplicates can do,

00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:44.820
I can do.

00:17:44.820 --> 00:17:49.409
So [INAUDIBLE] gives me
some kind of satisfaction.

00:17:49.409 --> 00:17:51.200
PAVNI DIWANJI: So much
for showing the way.

00:17:51.200 --> 00:17:51.700
Great.

00:17:51.700 --> 00:17:52.750
I think it's great.

00:17:52.750 --> 00:17:55.950
I think the Google team wanted
to know what's next for you.

00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:57.200
What's the next big challenge?

00:17:57.200 --> 00:18:01.579
Are we going to see you guys
in some romantic role, maybe?

00:18:01.579 --> 00:18:02.370
What's coming next?

00:18:02.370 --> 00:18:04.110
Give us something
that we can't--

00:18:04.110 --> 00:18:06.540
AJAY DEVGN: I'm starting
a film on our production.

00:18:06.540 --> 00:18:08.490
We're starting a film with her,
which is a fabulous script,

00:18:08.490 --> 00:18:09.440
and she's loved a lot.

00:18:09.440 --> 00:18:11.310
Like she just said
that she takes her time

00:18:11.310 --> 00:18:14.210
to choose a script, so--

00:18:14.210 --> 00:18:15.310
PAVNI DIWANJI: Yeah.

00:18:15.310 --> 00:18:17.589
So we'll actually be
able to see both of you?

00:18:17.589 --> 00:18:19.630
AJAY DEVGN: No, I won't
be in that film because--

00:18:19.630 --> 00:18:20.820
KAJOL: I tried to make him
do a cameo, or a passing

00:18:20.820 --> 00:18:22.320
shot, or something like that.

00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:23.153
PAVNI DIWANJI: Yeah.

00:18:23.153 --> 00:18:25.460
I think he should, right?

00:18:25.460 --> 00:18:28.239
Clap your hands, or stomp your
feet, if you want [INAUDIBLE].

00:18:28.239 --> 00:18:31.592
AUDIENCE: [APPLAUSE AND CHEERS]

00:18:32.550 --> 00:18:34.470
AUDIENCE MEMBER: [INAUDIBLE]

00:18:34.470 --> 00:18:35.315
KAJOL: Sorry?

00:18:35.315 --> 00:18:37.970
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:18:37.970 --> 00:18:38.470
KAJOL: See?

00:18:38.470 --> 00:18:38.800
AJAY DEVGN: Yeah.

00:18:38.800 --> 00:18:39.790
That's not a bad idea.

00:18:39.790 --> 00:18:40.230
KAJOL: I've been telling him.

00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:40.670
He told me, I got
married to you.

00:18:40.670 --> 00:18:41.460
That was enough.

00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:44.460
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:18:48.024 --> 00:18:49.940
PAVNI DIWANJI: I read
somewhere that you never

00:18:49.940 --> 00:18:55.050
left home without your sense
of humor, and it shows, right?

00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:58.700
So we've heard from
some global fan,

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:01.740
but you also have a
huge fan following

00:19:01.740 --> 00:19:04.800
in India, of course, and
also in Google in India.

00:19:04.800 --> 00:19:07.850
And so our next question is
going to come from a Googler

00:19:07.850 --> 00:19:09.625
all the way in Hyderabad.

00:19:09.625 --> 00:19:10.440
KAJOL: Wow.

00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:12.854
PAVNI DIWANJI: So could we
please roll the question?

00:19:12.854 --> 00:19:14.020
[? SHUP: Hello, ?] Ajay sir.

00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:15.370
Hello, Kajol ma'am.

00:19:15.370 --> 00:19:18.550
I am [? Shup, ?] and
I'm from Hyderabad.

00:19:18.550 --> 00:19:20.560
It's really a real
pleasure for me

00:19:20.560 --> 00:19:23.620
to get this opportunity
to ask you a question.

00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:27.355
And I have been a very
big fan of both of you,

00:19:27.355 --> 00:19:30.215
you know, since a long
time, ever since the "Pyaar

00:19:30.215 --> 00:19:31.830
To Hona Hi Tha" days.

00:19:31.830 --> 00:19:34.904
So today, the question I'm
going to ask is for both of you.

00:19:34.904 --> 00:19:38.260
And the question is, you have
both been in the industry

00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.240
for a very, very long time.

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:43.220
And during this time, there
has been a sea of changes.

00:19:43.220 --> 00:19:48.620
My question to both of you today
is, as established superstars,

00:19:48.620 --> 00:19:51.690
what do you both do to
keep up with these changes?

00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:53.860
Thank you.

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.722
AJAY DEVGN: Honestly?

00:19:55.722 --> 00:19:58.450
KAJOL: Very little.

00:19:58.450 --> 00:19:59.140
AJAY DEVGN: No.

00:19:59.140 --> 00:20:01.870
In fact, we learn a
lot from our kids.

00:20:01.870 --> 00:20:02.565
KAJOL: Yeah.

00:20:02.565 --> 00:20:04.814
AJAY DEVGN: And their friends,
and the new generation.

00:20:04.814 --> 00:20:08.240
I think it's very,
very important.

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:10.930
I don't even know how to
be on the net properly.

00:20:10.930 --> 00:20:13.150
I mean, whatever I learn
is from my daughter.

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:16.709
And when I ask her a question,
and she does something,

00:20:16.709 --> 00:20:17.750
I say, how did you do it?

00:20:17.750 --> 00:20:19.583
She says, don't ask me,
you old [INAUDIBLE].

00:20:19.583 --> 00:20:20.630
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:20:20.630 --> 00:20:22.296
AJAY DEVGN: So that's
the answer we get.

00:20:22.296 --> 00:20:23.380
They can do anything.

00:20:23.380 --> 00:20:24.382
So I think it's great.

00:20:24.382 --> 00:20:25.590
PAVNI DIWANJI: We can relate.

00:20:25.590 --> 00:20:26.260
I can relate, too.

00:20:26.260 --> 00:20:26.610
AJAY DEVGN: Of course.

00:20:26.610 --> 00:20:27.235
And it's great.

00:20:27.235 --> 00:20:29.570
And it's great you have
to learn from them.

00:20:29.570 --> 00:20:31.135
PAVNI DIWANJI:
That's the future.

00:20:31.135 --> 00:20:33.260
AJAY DEVGN: That's how you
keep upgrading yourself.

00:20:33.260 --> 00:20:34.260
PAVNI DIWANJI: That's
great. [INAUDIBLE]

00:20:34.260 --> 00:20:36.200
I think Kajol was
telling us, at the back,

00:20:36.200 --> 00:20:38.120
was that she's a
big Android fan.

00:20:38.120 --> 00:20:38.980
Can you believe it?

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:40.555
AUDIENCE: [CHEERING]

00:20:40.555 --> 00:20:41.930
PAVNI DIWANJI:
And she frequently

00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:46.060
has debates in the house,
because the kids like iPhones,

00:20:46.060 --> 00:20:48.200
and she loves Android.

00:20:48.200 --> 00:20:52.550
So we are thrilled to hear that.

00:20:52.550 --> 00:20:54.870
So this is a question.

00:20:54.870 --> 00:20:58.053
The next question is
related to the change.

00:20:58.053 --> 00:21:00.920
And we at Google are very
passionate about women's

00:21:00.920 --> 00:21:01.780
involvement.

00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:03.940
And I know both of you are.

00:21:03.940 --> 00:21:08.600
And I just saw the
"Parched" movie trailer

00:21:08.600 --> 00:21:10.940
that you released on YouTube.

00:21:10.940 --> 00:21:13.290
And it kind of moved me.

00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:15.840
It promises to-- I haven't
watched the full movie yet,

00:21:15.840 --> 00:21:18.340
and I'm really, really
looking forward to it.

00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:22.830
And a question first, for
you, Kajol, on the topic,

00:21:22.830 --> 00:21:24.930
is, it seems from
outside of Bollywood

00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:28.880
that the change is coming
slowly, in terms of respect,

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:31.650
and female actress
respect in Bollywood.

00:21:31.650 --> 00:21:32.420
KAJOL: It is.

00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:33.230
Definitely.

00:21:33.230 --> 00:21:37.420
And I think that's because,
like I said earlier on,

00:21:37.420 --> 00:21:39.610
that's because the
audience has changed.

00:21:39.610 --> 00:21:40.830
Not for any other reason.

00:21:40.830 --> 00:21:43.840
But, you know, when people start
turning around and spending

00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:47.120
money to go and watch a film,
which is not in the quote,

00:21:47.120 --> 00:21:50.150
unquote, "regular"
stream of films,

00:21:50.150 --> 00:21:52.740
or regular kind
of genre, I think

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:54.480
that's when that change
actually happens.

00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:56.930
And right now,
actually, I think it's

00:21:56.930 --> 00:21:59.090
an amazing time in
the film industry,

00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:02.530
because we have so many
different kinds of films

00:22:02.530 --> 00:22:03.480
being made.

00:22:03.480 --> 00:22:06.800
And it is now economically
feasible for them to be made.

00:22:06.800 --> 00:22:08.870
Because people are going
outside, watching them,

00:22:08.870 --> 00:22:09.855
enjoying them.

00:22:09.855 --> 00:22:12.230
Social media has a lot to do
with it, because they go out

00:22:12.230 --> 00:22:15.610
and they talk about it
on every media platform

00:22:15.610 --> 00:22:17.090
that they can find.

00:22:17.090 --> 00:22:20.120
And I think that, in
itself, makes it huge.

00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:24.740
That, you know, you don't have
that herd mentality anymore,

00:22:24.740 --> 00:22:27.235
to say that, you know,
if one person-- You know,

00:22:27.235 --> 00:22:28.760
nobody is making
money on this film,

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:30.750
because one person has
not liked the film.

00:22:30.750 --> 00:22:32.394
You have 100 different opinions.

00:22:32.394 --> 00:22:33.560
Everybody has their opinion.

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:36.894
And everybody can go out and
say that, I like this film.

00:22:36.894 --> 00:22:38.310
Let me go and watch
it, and let me

00:22:38.310 --> 00:22:40.270
take my 30, 40 friends with me.

00:22:40.270 --> 00:22:41.240
So, yeah.

00:22:41.240 --> 00:22:42.430
PAVNI DIWANJI: Yeah.

00:22:42.430 --> 00:22:45.570
As I was watching the trailer
for "Parched," I was moved,

00:22:45.570 --> 00:22:48.180
and, like, OK, this
is a story that we

00:22:48.180 --> 00:22:49.864
should have told a while ago.

00:22:49.864 --> 00:22:51.280
And I'm really
glad that someone--

00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:54.530
AJAY DEVGN: And the best part
is, the film is based in India.

00:22:54.530 --> 00:22:57.650
But, I mean, it's gone
all over the world.

00:22:57.650 --> 00:22:59.184
It's gone to 28--

00:22:59.184 --> 00:23:00.100
KAJOL: Film festivals.

00:23:00.100 --> 00:23:01.350
AJAY DEVGN: 28 film festivals.

00:23:01.350 --> 00:23:03.460
It's won 18 awards.

00:23:03.460 --> 00:23:06.860
And people, women,
people all over the world

00:23:06.860 --> 00:23:08.240
connect with this film.

00:23:08.240 --> 00:23:09.304
Some way or the other--

00:23:09.304 --> 00:23:10.720
KAJOL: From every
kind of strata--

00:23:10.720 --> 00:23:11.800
AJAY DEVGN: --they feel that--

