MONICA: And I'm Monica.

00:28:04.350 --> 00:28:06.025
And we're super
big fans of yours.

00:28:06.025 --> 00:28:10.350
And we were curious-- as
a high-profile couple,

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:13.290
how do you balance being a
couple with your careers?

00:28:15.884 --> 00:28:17.050
AJAY DEVGN: Going to answer?

00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:19.200
KAJOL: I will.

00:28:19.200 --> 00:28:20.660
No need to ask me that question.

00:28:20.660 --> 00:28:22.659
You have to stop me and
put a muzzle on my mouth

00:28:22.659 --> 00:28:24.260
most of the time.

00:28:24.260 --> 00:28:28.710
But I think this is something
that a lot of people ask us,

00:28:28.710 --> 00:28:29.960
the how do you balance?

00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:31.080
How do you make that?

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:32.300
How do you make it work?

00:28:32.300 --> 00:28:34.740
How do you make it OK every day?

00:28:34.740 --> 00:28:37.200
And I just have one
answer for that,

00:28:37.200 --> 00:28:40.470
because you have to
work at it every day.

00:28:40.470 --> 00:28:44.110
You can't decide that, OK, today
I'm taking a holiday from work.

00:28:44.110 --> 00:28:45.910
That's not going to happen.

00:28:45.910 --> 00:28:47.150
It's a relationship.

00:28:47.150 --> 00:28:50.680
It is your life, at
the end of the day.

00:28:50.680 --> 00:28:52.450
It's your kids, your husband.

00:28:52.450 --> 00:28:54.082
And whatever they are, they are.

00:28:54.082 --> 00:28:55.540
I mean, they are
my life, for sure.

00:28:55.540 --> 00:28:56.390
I don't know about
everybody else.

00:28:56.390 --> 00:28:57.610
But, yeah, they are my life.

00:28:57.610 --> 00:28:59.110
And when I'm talking
about, when I'm

00:28:59.110 --> 00:29:01.840
talking about balancing your
personal work and your family

00:29:01.840 --> 00:29:05.250
life together, it's a work
in progress every day.

00:29:05.250 --> 00:29:06.670
You put in that effort.

00:29:06.670 --> 00:29:09.080
You put in that little
extra every day.

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:12.140
And you have to put in a little
bit of extra for yourself,

00:29:12.140 --> 00:29:13.189
as well.

00:29:13.189 --> 00:29:14.730
I mean, there's no
two ways about it.

00:29:14.730 --> 00:29:18.130
If you don't put in that
little extra for yourself,

00:29:18.130 --> 00:29:19.480
you will feel shortchanged.

00:29:19.480 --> 00:29:21.280
And that's where all
the guilt starts.

00:29:21.280 --> 00:29:23.810
And that's where all those
horrible cycles start,

00:29:23.810 --> 00:29:25.720
where we don't want
to, you know, oh, god.

00:29:25.720 --> 00:29:26.710
I'm feeling martyred.

00:29:26.710 --> 00:29:28.876
And, oh, god, why I'm doing
all this and nobody else

00:29:28.876 --> 00:29:30.360
is helping me out, and all that.

00:29:30.360 --> 00:29:33.370
So I think, I honestly
believe, that everybody has

00:29:33.370 --> 00:29:35.860
to-- Every day is a new day.

00:29:35.860 --> 00:29:36.360
Every day.

00:29:36.360 --> 00:29:37.590
Some days, I'm a good mother.

00:29:37.590 --> 00:29:39.100
Some days, I'm
not a good mother.

00:29:39.100 --> 00:29:40.560
Some days I'm a better wife.

00:29:40.560 --> 00:29:44.020
Some days I'm a better actor.

00:29:44.020 --> 00:29:46.410
Some days I'm a
better multitasker.

00:29:46.410 --> 00:29:48.862
Some days I don't
finish my checklist

00:29:48.862 --> 00:29:50.320
that I wake up with
in the morning.

00:29:50.320 --> 00:29:53.650
So I think, forgive yourself
for whatever you're doing.

00:29:53.650 --> 00:29:56.360
We women are conditioned
to carry so much guilt

00:29:56.360 --> 00:29:58.650
from the time that
we're born, really.

00:29:58.650 --> 00:30:01.150
I think we need to learn how
to forgive ourselves, and teach

00:30:01.150 --> 00:30:02.200
our children that.

00:30:02.200 --> 00:30:03.075
PAVNI DIWANJI: Great.

00:30:03.075 --> 00:30:03.974
Hear, hear.

